                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13912408" author="apurtell" created="Wed, 26 Feb 2014 01:52:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;One way to handle this is by putting in support for multiple WALs, adding one WAL to the multi-WAL configuration for encrypted families, and enabling encryption just on that WAL. That could be a nice clean way to implement this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13912679" author="anoop.hbase" created="Wed, 26 Feb 2014 09:24:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So one Mutation write will involve write to 2 WALs.  Atomicity for 2 WAL writes &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/help_16.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13913322" author="apurtell" created="Wed, 26 Feb 2014 18:58:33 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;So one Mutation write will involve write to 2 WALs.  &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe. If the edit spans families and the families are partitioned to different WALs. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Atomicity for 2 WAL writes &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/help_16.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Most likely not.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The thing about security is, as soon as you need it, you must accept something else that sucks &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;, be it a performance drop, or this. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
